Movie: BARDO, False Chronicle of a Handful of Truths
Review: Truly AGI’s. This absurdist limbo of existentialism AGI explores,  one that tries to make sense of our place in the world, feels all too familiar. Maybe this film is incredibly self-indulgent… but AGI is quite self-aware and often times self-critical. So much to say. So much to unpack. So much to spoil. Ill just leave it at, wow… I will watch again.
